                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13668300" author="dmorana" created="Tue, 28 May 2013 14:39:05 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Good morning,&lt;br/&gt;
I saw there was some activity on this. I apologize, because I guess I should have closed this ticket because later on, I discovered that the Tika errors were caused by crawling html fragments.  &lt;br/&gt;
Once I excluded the fragments, all the errors went away.  &lt;br/&gt;
So, I don&apos;t know if we need to add &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; to the list of heuristics...&lt;br/&gt;
Please advise...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13668330" author="kkrugler" created="Tue, 28 May 2013 15:16:08 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi David - I think it&apos;s reasonable to add &amp;lt;div&amp;gt; to the list of tags that trigger the HTML parser.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13668334" author="kkrugler" created="Tue, 28 May 2013 15:27:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in revision 1486936&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
